{"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"LINK","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Automaton"}},"1":{"type":"LINK","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"href":"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/ElementaryCellularAutomaton.html"}},"2":{"type":"LINK","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"href":"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Rule30.html"}},"3":{"type":"LINK","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elementary_cellular_automaton"}},"4":{"type":"LINK","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"href":"https://twitter.com/imbanders"}},"5":{"type":"LINK","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"href":"https://www.last.fm/user/iBrianAnders"}},"6":{"type":"LINK","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"href":"https://github.com/briananders"}},"7":{"type":"LINK","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"href":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/andersbrian/"}}},"blocks":[{"key":"d5t7o","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"em36j","text":"Elementary Cellular Automaton","type":"header-one","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c4mhs","text":"Your browser does not support the canvas tag!","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3ca32","text":"If you've ever heard of Conway’s The Game of Life, you may already have an idea of what this is. If not, now worries, it’s not that crazy of a concept.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3hkor","text":"Wikipedia.org","type":"blockquote","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":13,"key":0}],"data":{}},{"key":"17qvi","text":"An automaton (plural: automata or automatons) is a self-operating machine, or a machine or control mechanism designed to automatically follow a predetermined sequence of operations, or respond to predetermined instructions.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d6sg1","text":"Cells are very basic. They are black or white. Alive or dead. Binary.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c2bbk","text":"The animation below, is a 1 dimensional world of cells. That one dimension is on the horizontal axis. Time is the vertical axis, moving from the top to the bottom.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cm5la","text":"The way life plays out in this world is absolutely declarative. The second line is derived from the first line, by a series of rules; the third from the second, and so on. There is no free will.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e58ii","text":"The rules are simple.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1jdmt","text":"Each \"world\" (or Automaton) starts with a single dark cell. I position it in the center.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fu2mh","text":"Each cell’s color, is decided by the 3 cells immediately above it","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6fi33","text":"The key to each world’s evolution is in the “rule”","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5gvnp","text":"Now let’s unpack what that means.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cn2jl","text":"Each cell’s color, is decided by the 3 cells immediately above it, in the shape of a capital T. Those three \"parents\" form a 3 digit binary sequence. 0 is white and 1 is black. There are 8 possible combinations of white and black values in a string of length 3.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9v70c","text":"000","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ci2ps","text":"001","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8fpmk","text":"010","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a66k2","text":"011","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"45c77","text":"100","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4kdek","text":"101","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7vioo","text":"110","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"abumd","text":"111","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ai31l","text":"Each world has a \"rule\" that everything is based on numbering from 0 to 255. This page is setup to start with Rule 90. All numbers from 0 to 255 can be represented by an 8 digit binary sequence. In this case, 90 is represented as 1011010.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4vjtc","text":"So a cell looks at its parents and uses their coloring as a look-up value against the main rule. If your parents are 101, you will select the 5th value from the right on the main rule’s binary value. If it is a 1, the cell is black. Otherwise, it is white.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"99ump","text":"Here are some links to other resources if you want to dig deeper into the subject.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2e7dd","text":"Wolfram.com Elementary Cellular Automaton","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":41,"key":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"9odbo","text":"Rule 30","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":7,"key":2}],"data":{}},{"key":"37o0s","text":"Wikipedia.org Elementary Cellular Automaton","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":43,"key":3}],"data":{}},{"key":"r1dh","text":"Rule number from 0 to 255: ▲ ▼","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9uuah","text":"Height: ▲ ▼","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bna32","text":"Random Start: Scroll?:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8t8sf","text":"© 2022","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ehkj2","text":"Twitter - Last.fm - Github - LinkedIn","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":7,"key":4},{"offset":10,"length":7,"key":5},{"offset":20,"length":6,"key":6},{"offset":29,"length":8,"key":7}],"data":{}}]}